      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To delve deeper into the \"rule of law\" aspect, your students could argue that lax border enforcement erodes the moral legitimacy of the US immigration system by implicitly condoning lawlessness and disregard for national borders. They could invoke the concept of \"ius sapientiae\" (the law of the wise), a Latin phrase emphasizing that the effectiveness and popularity of a law are directly linked to its perceived legitimacy and authority.\n\nIn this framework, American immigration policies might be viewed as ambiguous and subject to endless interpretation when once-secret corridors of discretion are opened and lax enforcement becomes the dominant approach. By asserting greater border control, the US effectively affirms its claim to an efficacious and organized rule of law.",
